  "number": 5586,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5586",
  "title": "Catch all routes with \"react-instantsearch-hooks-router-nextjs\" do not work",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nCatch all routes with \"react-instantsearch-hooks-router-nextjs\" do not work. The browser button does not work at all.\r\n\r\n@aymeric-giraudet I tried solving it with your beforePopState solution. But this does not even get triggered. \n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\nCreate a [...all].js in pages.js\r\n\r\nThen make the instant search pages use the same catch all route as the hit.\r\n\r\nThe fix is in https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/blob/master/packages/instantsearch.js/src/lib/routers/history.ts =>\r\n\r\nProblem is\r\n\r\n`  public dispose(): void {\r\n    if (this._dispose) {\r\n      this._dispose();\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    this.isDisposed = true;\r\n\r\n    safelyRunOnBrowser(({ window }) => {\r\n      if (this._onPopState) {\r\n        window.removeEventListener('popstate', this._onPopState);\r\n      }\r\n    });\r\n\r\n    if (this.writeTimer) {\r\n      clearTimeout(this.writeTimer);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    this.write({} as TRouteState);\r\n  }`\r\n\r\nThis last rule should not be there for next to work.\r\n\r\n`\r\n    this.write({} as TRouteState);\r\n`\r\nWhen I comment this line everything works as expected.\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/github/algolia/instantsearch.js/tree/templates/react-instantsearch\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nCatch all routes with getStaticProps should work.\n\n### Package version\n\nnext 13.3.0, react-instantsearch-hooks-router-nextjs 6.42.1, react-instantsearch-hooks-server 6.42.1, react-instantsearch-hooks-web 6.42.1\n\n### Operating system\n\n_No response_\n\n### Browser\n\n_No response_\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [X] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
